headline: Is Deere’s Precision Agriculture Push Justifying the Current Share Price in 2025?
summary: If you are wondering whether Deere is still a buy after its long run, you are not alone. This breakdown will help you decide if the current price makes sense or if patience might pay off. Despite a solid long term track record, with shares up 86.8% over five years and 13.2% over three, the stock has cooled recently, slipping 2.8% over the last week and 4.1% over the past month, while still sitting 11.8% higher year to date and 9.5% over the last year.
